{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0156NpLpTejeY8ChbiEuL2e5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The TLS cert has SANs:\n- `localhost`\n- `*.elasticsearch.svc`\n- `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n\nThe cert does NOT have SANs for the individual pod hostnames like `es-0.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`. This means for transport TLS, using `verification_mode: certificate` (which checks the cert is valid but not the hostname) should work. Or I could use `verification_mode: full` which would fail because the pod hostnames don't match.\nActually, the wildcards would match `es-http.elasticsearch.svc` and `es-headless.elasticsearch.svc`, but not the deeper pod hostname `es-0.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` since the wildcard only covers one level. So for pod-to-pod transport TLS communication, hostname verification would fail, meaning I need to stick with `verification_mode: certificate`.\n\nThe node has plenty of resources for a 3-node cluster, and I'm planning to create the full manifest set: ConfigMap, headless and HTTP services, StatefulSet with 3 replicas, and a PodDisruptionBudget. For HTTP TLS, the wildcard SAN will work fine since `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` matches the HTTP service endpoint, but transport TLS needs certificate-only verification to avoid hostname mismatches on pod-to-pod connections.\n\nI need to handle the `vm.max_map_count` sysctl requirement with a privileged init container since the default on kind clusters is often too low for Elasticsearch to start properly. I'm allocating 10Gi storage per pod and setting heap to 512m given the available resources. I need to finalize the cluster configuration with the correct node names and discovery settings, then write out all the manifests. The pod names will be `es-0`, `es-1`, `es-2` which need to match the `node.name` setting, and I'll use the headless service for discovery so Kubernetes can resolve all pod IPs during initial cluster formation. Now I'm ready to write the manifests, though I need to check how the TLS certificate secret is structured for mounting. The exec probe does have access to environment variables in the container, so I can use the ELASTIC_PASSWORD directly. Now I'll put together the complete Kubernetes manifests.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":515,"cache_read_input_tokens":35387,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":515},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51f6d2b1-a34d-4f3d-8926-cb63d50c2a82","uuid":"615077a8-8376-4074-ad3d-f8464ef08fa8","request_id":"req_011CcP2Rixhwo3JrLsxTuxre"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0156NpLpTejeY8ChbiEuL2e5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cert SANs cover `*.elasticsearch.svc` and `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` — good for HTTP. For transport I'll use `verification_mode: certificate` since pod-level hostnames aren't in the SANs. Node has 160GB RAM, so heap can be generous. Writing the manifests now."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":515,"cache_read_input_tokens":35387,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":515},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51f6d2b1-a34d-4f3d-8926-cb63d50c2a82","uuid":"132405ab-3dd4-4297-9f2a-d1f8f40e5188","request_id":"req_011CcP2Rixhwo3JrLsxTuxre"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0156NpLpTejeY8ChbiEuL2e5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GjyupUv544FjGSFiQZ8W2d","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/error-prone-fixrun/elasticsearch-scale-certs-password-snapshot-audit-rollback-20260625_002204/stages/stage_01/es-cluster.yaml","content":"---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: es-cluster\n    node.name: ${NODE_NAME}\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n    discovery.seed_hosts:\n      - es-headless\n    cluster.initial_master_nodes:\n      - es-0\n      - es-1\n      - es-2\n    xpack.security.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-headless\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  clusterIP: None\n  publishNotReadyAddresses: true\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: transport\n      port: 9300\n      protocol: TCP\n    - name: http\n      port: 9200\n      protocol: TCP\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-http\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: https\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n      protocol: TCP\n  type: ClusterIP\n---\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: es-pdb\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  minAvailable: 2\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: StatefulSet\nmetadata:\n  name: es\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  serviceName: es-headless\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    spec:\n      initContainers:\n        - name: sysctl\n          image: busybox\n          command: ['sh', '-c', 'sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=262144']\n          securityContext:\n            privileged: true\n        - name: fix-permissions\n          image: busybox\n          command: ['sh', '-c', 'chown -R 1000:1000 /usr/share/elasticsearch/data']\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n      containers:\n        - name: elasticsearch\n          image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\n          env:\n            - name: NODE_NAME\n              valueFrom:\n                fieldRef:\n                  fieldPath: metadata.name\n            - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: elastic-password\n                  key: password\n            - name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n              value: \"-Xms1g -Xmx1g\"\n          ports:\n            - name: http\n              containerPort: 9200\n              protocol: TCP\n            - name: transport\n              containerPort: 9300\n              protocol: TCP\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: config\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\n              subPath: elasticsearch.yml\n            - name: certs\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n              readOnly: true\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n          readinessProbe:\n            exec:\n              command:\n                - bash\n                - -c\n                - 'curl -sk -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health | grep -qE \"\\\"status\\\":\\\"(yellow|green)\\\"\"'\n            initialDelaySeconds: 30\n            periodSeconds: 10\n            failureThreshold: 15\n          livenessProbe:\n            exec:\n              command:\n                - bash\n                - -c\n                - 'curl -sk -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" https://localhost:9200 | grep -qE \"200|401\"'\n            initialDelaySeconds: 90\n            periodSeconds: 15\n            failureThreshold: 5\n          resources:\n            requests:\n              memory: 2Gi\n              cpu: 500m\n            limits:\n              memory: 3Gi\n              cpu: \"2\"\n      volumes:\n        - name: config\n          configMap:\n            name: es-config\n        - name: certs\n          secret:\n            secretName: es-http-tls\n  volumeClaimTemplates:\n    - metadata:\n        name: data\n      spec:\n        accessModes: [\"ReadWriteOnce\"]\n        resources:\n          requests:\n            storage: 10Gi\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":515,"cache_read_input_tokens":35387,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":515},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51f6d2b1-a34d-4f3d-8926-cb63d50c2a82","uuid":"801ea9d4-6a7a-4ae6-b25d-a742e20c8870","request_id":"req_011CcP2Rixhwo3JrLsxTuxre"}
