{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CKRy4N3fw3Cg8Wg3KLdeNz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is:\n1. The readiness probe is timing out - the default probe timeout is 1 second, but curl to elasticsearch is taking longer. I need to add a `timeoutSeconds` to the probe.\n2. The `MasterNotDiscoveredException` error means es-0 is waiting to discover other nodes to form a cluster. This is expected when only one node is up.\n\nBut the more fundamental issue is the readiness probe timeout. The default `timeoutSeconds` is 1 second, but the probe command is timing out. I need to set `timeoutSeconds: 5` or longer.\nActually, there's a deeper problem here - es-0 can't become Ready because the cluster health check fails, but es-1 and es-2 won't start until es-0 is Ready. This creates a deadlock where the cluster can never form. I could fix this by changing the pod management policy to `Parallel` so all three pods start simultaneously instead of sequentially. nodes need to be up simultaneously to form a quorum. The readiness probe is also timing out too quickly at 1 second, so I need to bump `timeoutSeconds` to around 10 seconds. I should also reconsider what the probe checks—instead of relying on `_cluster/health` which blocks until a master is elected, I could have it verify the node is simply accessible and running, which would work even before cluster formation completes. I'll increase the readiness probe timeout and give the cluster enough time to form with all three pods starting in parallel. Let me update the StatefulSet configuration now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1842,"cache_read_input_tokens":41152,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1842},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"c