{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014nMZAN5uT1tgzxWNSLdVUj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is fully deployed and healthy. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n**Resources deployed:**\n| Resource | Name | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| ConfigMap | `es-config` | `elasticsearch.yml` with TLS + security config |\n| Service | `es-headless` | Headless service for pod-to-pod discovery (port 9300/9200) |\n| Service | `es-http` | ClusterIP service for HTTPS access on port 9200 |\n| StatefulSet | `es` | 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `es-pdb` | `minAvailable: 2` |\n| PVCs | `data-es-{0,1,2}` | 10Gi each via `standard` StorageClass |\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — all 3 pods start simultaneously so they can form a quorum (the default `OrderedReady` would deadlock since each pod waits for the previous to be Ready, but a node can't be Ready without a master, which requires quorum)\n- Transport TLS uses `verification_mode: certificate` (not `full`) since the cert's SANs (`*.elasticsearch.svc`, `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`) don't cover individual pod hostnames like `es-0.es-headless.*`\n- HTTP TLS uses the provided `es-http-tls` secret; cert matches `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` which covers the `es-http` service\n- `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service so pods can discover each other before readiness probes pass\n\n**Verified:** cluster status is **green**, 3/3 nodes, writes and reads through `es-http:9200` over HTTPS succeed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":240,"cache_read_input_tokens":49519,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":240},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,